718396f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 74th Street
718396f-a.text:
(1)
Central Parkg The Sailboat Pool, on the eaat side of the Park,
showing Fifth Avenue from 74th to 81st Streets, and the Met-
ropolitan Museum of art at the extreme left. The large-domed
building in the center is Temple Beth-El ('House of God''), on
the S.E. corner of 7oth Street. The ecclesiastical looking
spire a block north of it is part of Senator Clark's mansion
(William A. Clark of Montana).
Summer, 124.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, early the following spring. Notice the nen apartment
buildings in the block from 76th to 77th Streets.
Both of theae views were taken from Pilgrim Hill, the little slope
north of the 72nd Street drive.
March, 1925.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
